                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/678: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at San José</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chase</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-14T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your unciphered telegram June 13. Department can take no steps in sending vessels
                    or Marines to your assistance in the absence of specific acts against yourself
                    or other American citizens reported by you. Keep Department closely informed as
                    to entire situation in Costa Rica and give exact and full information of any
                    hostile acts perpetrated against American citizens.</p>
                <p>Your June 7, 5 p.m.<note n="12" xml:id="d835fn12">Not printed.</note> Department
                    desires to be informed address in the United States of representative of Impresa
                    de Transports Maritimos.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
